cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.SY, cs.CV

This paper is about a reinforcement learning algorithm that combines model-free and model-based approaches to improve exploration and learning in environments with sparse rewards. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), which includes papers on reinforcement learning and deep learning. The paper also discusses the use of supervised learning to learn the dynamics of the environment, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the algorithm involves planning and decision-making, which could place it in cs.RO (Robotics) or cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper uses OpenAI gym environments, which involve visual inputs, so it could also be relevant to cs.CV (Computer Vision).
